# Frontend & Assets

- Use **Tailwind CSS** for layout and styling; prefer utility classes and existing design patterns over one-off inline styles.
- Use **Hotwire**: Turbo for navigation and partial updates; **Stimulus** for discrete client behavior. Avoid heavy client-side frameworks unless the project already depends on them.
- Manage modern JS/CSS through **Vite** (`ruby-vite`). Put entry points and packs where the app already expects them; do not bypass the build for production assets.
- Keep views mostly free of business logic: use helpers, presenters, or view components when presentation logic grows.
- User-facing copy should go through **I18n** where the rest of the app does; avoid hardcoding long strings in multiple places.
- Respect accessibility: semantic HTML, labels for forms, sufficient contrast. Prefer progressive enhancement with Turbo.
